		<material name="Vespel SP-1" description="Unfilled polyimide" propertysource="Dupont Vespel S Line Design Guide, H-53668-2 (09/22)" appdata="Assumptions:&#xA;1. Using DuPont's properties for parts machined out of isostatic material (not direct formed)&#xA;2. elastic modulus ~ flexural modulus&#xA;3. tensile strength ~ D1708 ultimate tensile (not E8)&#xA;4. compressive strength ~ compressive stress @ 10% strain&#xA;5. yield strength ~ compressive stress @ 0.1% offset&#xA;6. properties are generally at 23C (note DuPont also provides some props at 260C)&#xA;&#xA;Other properties:&#xA;1. Dynamic friction coefficient in air = 0.29 @ 0.875 MPa*m/s&#xA;2. Static friction coefficient in air = 0.35&#xA;3. Axial fatigue endurance limit = 55.8 MPa @ 10^3 cycles, 42.1 MPa @ 10^7&#xA;4. Flexural fatigue endurance limit = 65.5 MPa @ 10^3 cycles, 44.8 MPa @ 10^7&#xA;&#xA;Equivalents:&#xA;Meldin 7001 is an unfilled polyimide which is closely equivalent to Vespel SP-1.">
